definition.value: An anthocyanin cation that is pelargonidin in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is substituted by a 6-O-[(2E)-3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)prop-2-enoyl]-beta-D-glucopyranosyl group and the hydroxy group at position 5 is substituted by a 4,6-bis-O-(carboxyacetyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A hydroxyisoflavone, isoflavone dimer obtained from Ficus mucuso.
A hydroxyisoflavone, isoflavone dimer obtained from Ficus mucuso.
A hydroxyisoflavone, isoflavone dimer obtained from Ficus mucuso.

A  hydroxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 7 and a 6,6-dimethyl-3,6-dihydro-2H-pyran across positions 3' and 4' respectively. It has been isolated from Ficus mucuso.
A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is isoflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7 and 4' and a prenyl group at position 3'. It has been isolated from Ficus mucuso.
